&lt;p&gt;Auxillary files can be placed in the &lt;code&gt;content&lt;/code&gt; folder, i.e. &lt;code&gt;aux&lt;/code&gt; and linked to in yaml header:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&#34;r&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;csl: aux/apa.csl
css: aux/APAStyle.css
keep_md: yes
bibliography: aux/lifeevents.bib&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rmarkdown will then use this to produce html file in &lt;code&gt;public/post&lt;/code&gt; folder. At least bibtex file, not so sure about css though…&lt;/p&gt;
